 ashtray so that it would go on burning. Its ends squirmed, blackened.

'You will excuse me,' he said, 'for having yielded to a movement of affection and exaltation. See this scar?'

He showed the back of his hand.

'This,' he said, 'I received in a duel, in Hungary, four years ago. We used cavalry sabres. In spite of my several wounds, I managed to kill my opponent. He was a great man, a brilliant brain, a gentle heart, but he had had the misfortune of jokingly referring to my young sister as "